1. Meningitis: This is a serious infection of the membranes that cover the brain and spinal cord. Symptoms include fever

and sensitivity to light.
2. Encephalitis: This is an inflammation of the brain. Symptoms include fever

and personality changes.
3. Subarachnoid hemorrhage: This is a type of stroke that occurs when a blood vessel in the brain bursts. Symptoms include sudden onset of severe headache

and stiff neck.
4. Brain tumor: This is a growth of abnormal cells in the brain. Symptoms can vary depending on the size and location of the tumor

and changes in personality or behavior.
5. Cerebral aneurysm: This is a weak spot in a blood vessel in the brain. Symptoms may include headache

and changes in vision.
6. Arteriovenous malformation (AVM): This is a tangle of abnormal blood vessels in the brain. Symptoms may include headache

and changes in vision.
7. Cavernous malformation: This is a type of vascular malformation that occurs in the brain. Symptoms may include headache

and changes in vision.
8. Multiple sclerosis (MS): This is a chronic autoimmune disease that affects the central nervous system. Symptoms can vary depending on the severity of the disease

and difficulty with balance and coordination.
9. Guillain-Barré syndrome (GBS): This is an autoimmune disorder that affects the peripheral nervous system. Symptoms include weakness

and difficulty with walking and breathing.
